results.description: Buckhurst Hill is a suburban town in the Epping Forest district of Essex. A small part of the town comes under the London Borough of Redbridge, and in turn forms part of the Greater London Urban Area.  (...)
results.title: Buckhurst Hill

results.description: The London Borough of Redbridge (pronunciation) is a London borough in the north east sub-region of Greater London, England and forms part of Outer London. Its administrative headquarters is at Redbridge Town Hall in Ilford. The local authority is Redbridge London Borough Council.  (...)
results.title: London Borough of Redbridge
